newtab - open a workspace tab
Executable: /bin/newtab.sh
Alias: newtab

DESCRIPTION
  Opens a new tab running the
  ReMinux workspace UI in the
  current multishell session.

USAGE
  newtab

NOTES
  newtab requires a CC: Tweaked
  shell environment that
  exposes shell.openTab(), which
  is normally available only on
  advanced computers and inside
  multishell-aware launchers
  such as the workspace UI.

  On normal computers, turtles
  or pocket computers without
  multishell support, newtab
  prints a notice and exits
  without doing anything; this
  matches CC: Tweaked behaviour
  rather than crashing.

  Internally newtab calls
  minux.safeOpenTab(), which
  falls back to a single-shell
  run when openTab is not
  available.

SEE ALSO
  workspace - launch the UI
  bash      - plain shell
